<subSubSection id="C328ABCEFFA948187BB0FED8FBD64EC7" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFA948187BB0FED8FE954E3A" blockId="20.[189,310,264,290]" box="[189,310,264,290]" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">
<heading id="D0C54F29FFA948187BB0FED8FE954E3A" bold="true" box="[189,310,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA948187BB0FED8FE954E3A" bold="true" box="[189,310,264,290]" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8DF845FFA948187BB0FEE7FBD64EC7" blockId="20.[187,1399,311,479]" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">
Species with incomplete notauli like 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA948187965FEE7FD5F4E49" authorityName="Fergusson" authorityYear="1985" box="[616,764,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atricornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA948187965FEE7FD5F4E49" box="[616,764,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. atricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA948187806FEE7FC104E49" box="[779,947,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidiornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA948187806FEE7FC104E49" box="[779,947,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. flavidiornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA9481878EAFEE7FBCB4E49" box="[999,1128,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA9481878EAFEE7FBC04E49" authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1974" box="[999,1123,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">A. zaitzevi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA948187FCFFEE7FAD44E49" box="[1218,1399,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA948187FCFFEE7FAD44E49" box="[1218,1399,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. flavidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA948187BE3FE8BFEC44E6C" authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1974" box="[238,359,347,373]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA948187BE3FE8BFEC44E6C" box="[238,359,347,373]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. zaitzevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it presents an areolate scutellum (scutellum smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA9481878EAFE8BFB3F4E6C" box="[999,1180,346,373]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidicornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA9481878EAFE8BFB3F4E6C" box="[999,1180,346,373]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. flavidicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA948187FD9FE8BFAEE4E6C" authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1974" box="[1236,1357,347,373]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA948187FD9FE8BFAEE4E6C" box="[1236,1357,347,373]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. zaitzevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA94818790BFEAEFD3F4E8F" authorityName="Fergusson" authorityYear="1985" box="[518,668,382,408]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atricornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA94818790BFEAEFD3F4E8F" box="[518,668,382,408]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. atricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; however, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA94818782DFEAEFC364E8F" authorityName="Belizin" authorityYear="1961" box="[800,917,382,408]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paucus">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA94818782DFEAEFC364E8F" box="[800,917,382,408]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. paucus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has almost effaced notauli and posterior carina of scutellar foveae weakening in its central area (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3283C6FFA94818787EFE71FBA94EA2" authorityName="Fergusson" authorityYear="1985" box="[883,1034,417,443]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Aegilips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atricornis">
<emphasis id="B9462457FFA94818787EFE71FBA94EA2" box="[883,1034,417,443]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="128">A. atricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the notauli though incomplete are strongly apparent and basal carina of scutellar foveae is strong throughout).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
